I have now located the issue:

In lib/xlsx/xform/book/workbook-xform.js, it appears there has been some attempt to address the issue with the target attribute.  At some point the Target relationship gets converted to the "../" path:

```
      // if rel.Target start with `[space]/xl/` or `/xl/` , then it will be replaced with `''` and spliced behind `xl/`,
      // otherwise it will be spliced directly behind `xl/`. i.g.
      worksheet = model.worksheetHash[`xl/${rel.Target.replace(/^(\s|\/xl\/)+/, '')}`];
```

Then in lib/xlsx/xform/sheet/worksheet-xform.js reconcile function, the rels array includes the original /x1/ target, so the lookup to options.tables (which has the "../" change) fails:

```
      model.tables = (model.tables || []).map(tablePart => {
        const rel = rels[tablePart.rId];
        return options.tables[rel.Target];
      });
```

Potential fix (I suspect I may be oversimplifying the problem/solution, so I'm reluctant to create a push request):

lib/xlsx/xform/sheet/worksheet-xform.js|506
`return options.tables[rel.Target.replace(/^(\/xl)/, '..')];`
